an early fantasy novel, as the central character goes boldly to distant places outside the known world and meets, fights with, and learns from strange and alien creatures, before returning to the "real" world. The second, a novella, is ostensibly about chivalric bravery, but it is set in a pre-chivalric period, and shows how (then as now) a trivial incident can escalate towards disaster. The third is an animal fable, part of the extensive tradition of Reynard the Fox, initially familiar, but developing into a violent and dark tale that ends with the death of a king.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aGerman literatureyMiddle High German, 1050-1500vTranslations into English. 0aTaleszGermanyvTranslations into English. 0aTales, MedievalvTranslations into English. 4aGerman History. 4aMedieval German Literature. 4aMedieval Literature. 4aPolitics & Economics. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh  aOtto mit dem Bart.  aOtto the Great.  aReinhart Fuchs.  aanarchy.  acrisis.  adiplomacy.  afeudal system.  aimperialism.  anobility.  apardon.  apeace.  asatire.  ascoundrel.  atrickster.  averse.1 aMurdoch, Brian, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBoydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package 2024z978311143096640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781805433071?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781805433071423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781805433071/original  a978-3-11-143096-6  Boydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package 2024b2024  aGBV-deGruyter-alles